  "prompt": "Does a senator get security protection?",
  "response": "Yes, U.S. Senators receive security protection, especially when they are subject to credible threats or in response to specific incidents. The U.S. Capitol Police are responsible for the security of members of Congress, and they assess the level of risk and may provide protective details as needed. Additionally, Senators can request enhanced security measures for themselves and their families in certain situations, especially if there are threats against them due to their political activities or decisions. Security measures can include personal security details, improved security at their residences, and enhanced safety protocols during public appearances.",
